summary: 03/16/1993: Tahar Hamdi, an Algerian Minister for Work and Social Affairs was injured in an assassination attempt. There was no claim of responsibility. This attack was apart of a multiple incident see event ID#'s 199303140001, 199303160002, and 199303170002 for more information.
corp1: Algerian Ministry for Work and Social Affairs
addnotes: One injury and no casualties resulted from the attack. See event ID 199303170002 for more information.
scite1: Rachid Khiari, “New Slaying of High-Ranking Official as Terror Wave Continues,” The Associated Press, March 17, 1993.
scite3: “Algerian terrorism mounts; top government adviser slain,” Chicago Tribune, March 18, 1993.
